profile:
Baeumler Approved and a Certified Master Inspector, Bryce Rankin believes that knowing your home is key to making a good and safe investment for both you and your family. During the home inspection process clients are encouraged to follow along and ask questions. Being involved in this process gives clients a much better understanding of how the home operates and how to maintain it over the years.
Our detailed Home Inspections reports provide our clients with all the necessary information to make an informed home purchase. With digital reporting it is quick and easy to share your report with family, friends, or contractors to aid in any work or opinions that may be required to move forward comfortably with your investment. Technology is key. Thermal Imaging and Moisture Detection equipment used on all of our inspections can reveal defects that cannot be seen by the human eye. Revealing potential trouble spots throughout the home that can lead to significant cost and frustration down the road. In many cases these defects are hidden from view with a fresh coat of paint, drywall, or storage. Whether a home buyer, seller, or owner we can help. Online booking through our website is available 24/7 or you can contact Bryce Rankin at anytime to discuss your home inspection needs.

Property Condition Assessment (PCA)

ASTM E2018-15 establishes guidelines for performing a property condition assessment (PCA), Our field observers who specialize in PCA's typically performs a walk-through survey, interviews maintenance workers and tenants, and pulls courthouse documents like surveys and other technical data on the structure. All the information provides an overview of the building’s condition providing the client with a property condition report.

Commercial Building Inspection

Commercial building inspections differ from PCAs in that they provide much more detailed information to the client. We use the assistance of a team of experts, each of whom contributes information compiled in a highly detailed inspection report for the client. Get It Inspected on an office building we might bring in a structural engineer, elevator expert, and someone who understands fire protection systems, and on a small apartment building, we might not bring any of those consultants on board.

Whatever options you need, call us today to discuss the scope of work.

profile:
FREE Thermal Imaging* + FREE Long-term Radon Test with every inspection!

Knowledge doesn’t come about from fear; it comes from understanding. Confidence is built by knowing something thoroughly.

And that’s how New Century Home Inspection sets itself apart from the rest.

With over 20 years of construction and renovation experience, we understand that homeowners need a conversation that goes above and beyond a half-day visit and a report. We have developed our exclusive, RENO ASSIST, for homeowners who want answers from an experienced builder who won’t be attaching a quote or bid for service with their view of the space. We will come back, when you own the home, to discuss the implications of any defects that we discover, in greater detail than a one day inspection can allow.

We understand the need for a conversation.

There is no other home inspection company that offers this level of service.

We take our time. We only book one inspection per inspector, per day. This insures our ability to deliver an unparalleled level of service to our customers. We follow up and we make time. If you’re looking for a fast inspection with a quick report, we offer you every other home inspection company for your consideration.

*Certified Infrared Thermographer Level 1 Building Investigations (ITC)
